    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Long sleeves with a series of puffs that diminish in size from the shoulder to the wrist. The style was popular in Paris under the First Empire, ca.1804-1814, and was named for the Egyptian cavalry of Mamelukes led by Napoleon I.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
